=== SESSION PATCH NOTES [SESSION 10 — SEVENTEEN YEARS OF PENDING] ===
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GM INTENT (for future GMs):
This session was a pivot: from acquisition to consolidation. Anchor spent eight sessions stealing. This session, he built.
Thematic core: Doors. Thresholds. The moment waiting becomes choosing.
Key defections—not recruited through violence or debt, but possibility:
• Orpheus: 650k¥ for a dynasty. She doesn't know his name. She knows his trajectory. [THE TABLE]
• Veld: "What's my other option?" A door. He walks. [DE-ACCESSED] → [LEARNING TO LISTEN]
• Chen: Seventeen years of routes, ending in a room he was never meant to see. Anchor gives him purpose anyway.
• Miriam: Nineteen years of ledgers, finally finding the line item that doesn't balance. Ninety seconds of burn time. That's not loyalty. That's reckoning.
• Dr. Arisawa: Seventeen years of [PENDING]. A daughter who thinks her mother is dead. A ghost who walks through her door and says, "You don't have to be the Archivist's hand anymore."
Anchor is no longer just a thief. He's a custodian. A king without a castle, building one from abandoned warehouses and people who forgot they could choose.
Mechanical anchors:
• Georgetown terminal takeover (Hardware + Logic, Threshold 4) → Persistent Advantage. System recognizes him.
• Data purge (Computer, Threshold 5) → Dr. Arisawa's termination logs destroyed. No going back.
• Asset acquisition: Chrysalis, Morph, Eidolon, Subject Files 01-23 → Charter interest escalates from "asset recovery" to "existential threat."
Dr. Arisawa is not an asset. She is a moral witness. Her thread is [RELATION], not [INTEL] or [ACTION]. Yuki's birthday is in three weeks. If Anchor helps her walk through that door, it will be the campaign's most meaningful victory. If he doesn't, she will still love him—but she will always wonder if she's still waiting.
Be kind to her. She has waited long enough.
